commit.message: Remove six from document generation - see if the docs start building again.
Bump version to 2.0.2.
Remove unnecessary casts.
Fix #137 - fix type hint on raises() to Type[Exception].

Fix type hints for matchers taking nested matchers.

Use `Union[Matcher[T], T]` rather than `Union[T, Matcher[T]]`. The latter way, the `T` picks up all types, and the `Matcher[T]` is never picked up.
Update change log for 2.0.1, bump version number, and update copyright year.
Bring CHANGES.txt up to 2.0.0 version.
Make hamcrest package PEP 561 compatible.
Blacken
Mark Python 3.5+ only
Set version to 1.10 for release, and update copyright year.
Add python 3.8 to release script.
Bring CHANGES.txt up to 1.10 version.
Bring CHANGES.txt up to 1.9 version.
raises() grows support for additional matchers on exception object.

No newline in raises() with pattern mismatch desc.

Message change prepares for supporting additional messages from
matchers against the excepton object. Also, add test for raises()
with pattern mismatch message.
Build fix - bump OSX job to python 3.7.

commit.message: Annotations for new describe_match() method.
Additional type hint improvements.
Type annotations for library matchers.
Type annotations for core matchers.
Naive type annotations for base types.
Add mypy type checking target to tox & travis.
Pin tool versions on tox.ini.
Remove 3rd party mock library. As of Python 23, it's in the standard library.
Remove deprecated methods append_value and append_value_list.
Document describe_mismatch() and describe_match() on Custom Matcher page.
Use describe_match() in IsNot to better describe mismatches there, specifically in Raises.
Add describe_match() to Matcher and BaseMatcher.
